<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a619359-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s6734"><num value="6734">§ 6734.</num><heading> Other provisions</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7a61935a-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s6734/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Judicial review</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The appropriate United States district court shall have exclusive jurisdiction over litigation arising under this section <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002556">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002556"><num>1</num> See References in Text note below.</note> involving any redomesticating or redomesticated insurer.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7a61935b-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s6734/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Severability</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">If any provision of this section,<sup>1</sup> or the application thereof to any person or circumstances, is held invalid, the remainder of the section,<sup>1</sup> and the application of such provision to other persons or circumstances, shall not be affected thereby.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id7a61935c-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/102/tIII/s314">Pub. L. 106–102, title III, § 314</ref>, <date date="1999-11-12">Nov. 12, 1999</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/113/1420">113 Stat. 1420</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7a61935d-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7a61935e-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="id7a61935f-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">This section, referred to in text, probably should be a reference to this subtitle, meaning subtitle B (§§ 311–316) of title III of <ref href="/us/pl/106/102">Pub. L. 106–102</ref>, which is classified generally to this subchapter.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
